article.headline: Lafayette 35, Bucknell 14
article.story: EASTON, Pa. -- Rob Curley threw for 333 yards and three touchdowns to lead Lafayette to a 35-14 victory over Bucknell on Saturday. Curley, a senior, completed a career-high 30 passes out of 35 attempts as the Leopards (7-1, 3-0 Patriot League) won their sixth straight game. He threw scoring passes of 13 yards to Michael Bolton, 4 yards to Mitchell Bennett and 6 yards to Mark Layton. Lafayette, which entered ranked 14th in the Football Championship Subdivision in scoring defense (16.1 points) and 15th in rushing defense (90 yards), held Bucknell (3-5, 1-2) to 95 yards rushing. The Leopards scored 28 second-half points behind Curley, who threw all three of his touchdown passes in the second half. Marcello Trigg threw for 195 yards and a touchdown, and ran for a score, to lead Bucknell. A.J. Kizekai caught seven passes for 140 yards and a 19-yard touchdown pass from Trigg.
